<p>Now to sign a message with a Lamport signature we&#8217;ll first create a message digest by hashing the message with RIPEMD160 (in Bitcoin we would hash the transaction) then converting the output to binary. We&#8217;ll once again use &#8220;Hello World&#8221; as an example.</p>
<pre>Hello World ==&gt; a830d7beb04eb7549ce990fb7dc962e499a27230 ==&gt; 1010100000110000110101111011111010110000010011101011011101010100100111001110100110010000111110110111110111001001011000101110010010011001101000100111001000110000</pre>
<p>Next, we&#8217;ll match up each binary digit with each pair in our private key. If the bit is 0 we will add the first number in the pair to our signature, if it is 1 we&#8217;ll add the second.</p>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th width="20">Pair#</th>
