			<p>Thanks Natanael I&#8217;ll check it out.</p>
<p>Also, <a href="http://pqcrypto.org/" rel="nofollow">this</a> site seems to have a list of every academic paper on post-quantum cryptography ever written. </p>
<p>It seems to me though, that since hash functions are already heavily used and scrutinized, the hash-based systems are probably more ready for prime time than the others. Although I can&#8217;t really speak to the security of the others, the papers are very dense and hard to read. I&#8217;m sure that by the time quantum computers become a problem more of a consensus of the best algorithms will form.</p>

			</div>

